# Teaching Tips for Using LLMs in Class 

#### Engaging students in coding through interaction with AI not only captivates their interest but also enhances their critical thinking skills.



## Critical Thinking Integration
#### Don't treat LLM outputs as the final word. Teach students to: 

<details style="background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;">
    <summary style="font-size: 1.5em; font-weight: bold;">🎯 Evaluate Accuracy</summary>
<div style="margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;">
    <p style = "font-size: 16px;">
  Always fact-check information generated by the LLM, especially for factual writing tasks. <br><br> This skill can be practiced in <b>Lessons 3 and 5</b> as students can check the code suggestions the LLM gives them. 
</p></div>
</details>

<details style="background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;">
    <summary style="font-size: 1.5em; font-weight: bold;">🌐 Analyze Bias</summary>
<div style="margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;">
    <p style = "font-size: 16px;">
  Discuss how LLMs might inherit biases from their training data. Encourage students to be critical of any suggestions that seem biased. <br><br> This skill can be practiced in <b>Lesson 2 and Lesson 5</b> as the students filter through the ideas created by the LLM.  
</p></div>
</details>

<details style="background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;">
    <summary style="font-size: 1.5em; font-weight: bold;">🧠 Explain Reasoning</summary>
<div style="margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;">
    <p style = "font-size: 16px;">
  Emphasize the importance of understanding the "why" behind code or writing, not just blindly accepting LLM suggestions. <br><br> Students can practice this skill in <b>Lesson 3</b> by explaining the algorithms they worked on with the AI. 
  
</p></div>
</details>



MARKDOWN
